Occupy Sebastopol seeks support, protests big banks
Occupy Sebastopol demonstrators put their voices, and their feet, in the back of the movement on Saturday.
Tim Ryan, 23, of the west county, protests with Occupy Sebastopol on Saturday outdoor Wells Fargo Bank. (KENT PORTER/PD)
Two days after the Santa Rosa City Council gave Occupy campers permission to remain on the lawn at City Hall if they meet a range of conditions, shut to 60 marchers in Sebastopol dispensed fliers at shops and workplaces alongside several blocks of downtown.
They hope enterprise proprietors will put up them as pre-printed statements of aid in improve of a Tuesday meeting at Sebastopol City Hall over their right to camp in the central square.
